text:
Ordered a 6 piece fried chicken meals at 7am. The chicken is Korean style, so there is some sour mixed with the fried chicken. And it might look a bit darker than usual.
The chicken is small and a bit dry out in the middle. Sweet and spicy. You can taste the soy sauce and honey.
Honestly not the best fired chicken for the price. If Burger King had beef burger in breakfast menu, I’d get a burger instead. Sadly not so much options in the morning.

I went this restaurant with my girlfriend and we did not hear about it before. I took chicken burger and my girlfriend rice box with tofu as a combo. Food was delicious and quite cheap but meal size is not big. Old lady behind the desk was very friendly and lovely. I suggest everyone to try if you are looking this kind of food.

Winglets were not fresh, smelt like dry fish.  Deep fried until the meats were fully burnt.

Unfriendly staffs
Absolutely delicious! Do not miss out! I highly recommend their chicken and will definitely be coming back!
The food’s not bad. But except the old lady at the service counter, everyone else really need to work on their attitude.
